
[1]samphire

   SAM'PHIRE, n. [said to be a corruption of Saint Pierre.]

   A plant of the genus Crithmum. The golden samphire is of the genus
   Inula.

   Samphire grows on rocks near the sea shore, where it is washed by the
   salt water. It is used for pickling.
